      "Aux winch removed and shipped onshore for teardown inspection",
      "Metallurgical analysis conducted at Stress Laboratory",
      "Conex box lowered to gulf floor in safe zone"
    ],
    "summary": "On November 20, 2021, while offloading a Conex cargo box from an offshore supply vessel, the Front Runner's West crane auxiliary winch hoist failed, causing the Conex box to free fall 20-30 feet before striking the OSV and falling into offshore waters. The failure was caused by overloading and shock-loading of the crane, resulting in catastrophic failure of the ring gear due to multiple fatigue cracks.",
    "recommendations": [
      "Further evaluation of current Crane System design",
      "Review and revision of crane policies",
      "Implementation of suitable monitoring process ensuring workplace compliance"
    ],
    "key_phrases": [
      "aux winch failure",
      "ring gear fracture",
      "overloading",
      "shock-loading",
      "fatigue cracks"
    ]
